text: Amolops formosus (variously known as Assam sucker frog, beautiful stream frog, Assam cascade frog, or hill stream frog) is a species of frog found in high gradient streams of northern India, northern Bangladesh, and Nepal. ==References== formosus Category:Amphibians described in 1876 Category:Amphibians of Bangladesh Category:Frogs of India Category:Amphibians of Nepal
title: Amolops formosus
